    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-07T07:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-07T07:44:00-05:00" n="809"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/940: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-07T12:00:00-00:44"
                            >March 7, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Firestone had his first conference with the President March 5. It was merely a
                    courtesy call and there was no discussion of current problems. Next conference
                    will be March 11 when supplementary agreement<note n="10" xml:id="d809fn10">i.
                        e., agreement supplementary to the Loan Agreement of 1926, for text of which
                        see <ref target="frus1926v02#pg_574">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1926, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 574</ref>.</note> will be taken up.</p>
                <p>Strongly organized opposition party held national convention yesterday when
                    ex-President King was unanimously chosen to run against Barclay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
